---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SplitSection from '../components/SplitSection.astro';
import StackedSection from '../components/StackedSection.astro';
import HumanCenteredSection from '../components/HumanCenteredSection.astro';
import LeadingByExampleSection from '../components/LeadingByExampleSection.astro';
import ConnectSection from '../components/ConnectSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Lisa Wilkins | UX Design & Strategy"
  description="Lisa Wilkins is a UX Director, Product Strategist, and Agentic Builder with 17+ years building products for scale at NBCUniversal, PragerU, and Microsoft."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section
    class="relative flex flex-col items-start justify-end min-h-[340px] md:min-h-[380px] lg:min-h-[420px]"
    aria-labelledby="hero-heading"
  >
    <!-- Background layers -->
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[#EEEEEE] mix-blend-multiply"></div>
      <picture>
        <source
          type="image/webp"
          srcset="/images/home/home_bg_heading_1x.webp 1x, /images/home/home_bg_heading_2x.webp 2x"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/home/home-bg-heading.png"
          alt=""
          class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full max-w-none object-cover opacity-25 mix-blend-multiply"
        />
      </picture>
    </div>

    <!-- Frosted glass text bar -->
    <div class="backdrop-blur-[4px] bg-[rgba(252,250,244,0.6)] flex flex-col items-center justify-end py-5 relative shrink-0 w-full">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end gap-3 w-full max-w-5xl overflow-hidden px-5 py-[30px] text-[var(--color-blue-800)] rounded-lg">
        <h1
          id="hero-heading"
          class="font-light leading-none text-[44px] md:text-[56px] lg:text-[76px] flex-1 min-w-0"
        >
          Lisa Wilkins
        </h1>
        <p class="font-medium leading-normal text-[14px] md:text-[16px] text-right whitespace-pre shrink-0">Agentic Builder  |  UX Director  |  Product Strategist</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SplitSection
    id="nbc-heading"
    heading="Building for scale & flexibility"
    ctaLabel="View NBC App Redesign"
    ctaHref="/projects-nbcapp"
    imageSrc="/images/home/home-scale-nbc.png"
    imageSrcWebp="/images/home/home_scale_nbc_1x.webp"
    imageAlt="A collage of mobile app screens from NBC News brands"
    imageMaxWidth="575px"
  >
    <p slot="body" class="leading-[1.5] text-[var(--color-off-white)] text-[18px] md:text-[20px]">
      Solutions for NOW are valuable. Solutions for LATER pay you back. At NBCUniversal, I architected component systems and content frameworks across NBC News, TODAY, and Telemundo that supported 1.5M+ daily users, and kept scaling through two full app redesigns with a flexible foundation. That meant understanding the tech stack deeply enough to design for future growth.
    </p>
  </SplitSection>

  <StackedSection
    id="strategy-heading"
    heading="From complexity to clarity"
    ctaLabel="View Product Strategy Impact"
    ctaHref="/projects-puf"
    imageSrc="/images/home/home-complexity.png"
    imageSrcWebp="/images/home/home_complexity_1x.webp"
    imageAlt="A diagram showing product strategy and content organization work"
  >
    <p slot="body">
      I've made a career of stepping back, finding the signal, and building the simple, scalable structure underneath. Whether inherited or fresh earth, I bring the same approach: distill the chaos into foundational components, align the competing requirements, and deliver a system that serves the product long after the launch.
    </p>
    <p slot="body">
      I've built and inherited a platform serving 1.3M+ monthly users across web, mobile, and OTT with no unified content architecture. I distilled convoluted user journeys, organized content taxonomies, and broke down competing business requirements into foundational components — work that streamlined delivery cycles by 43% and extended well beyond any single release. The hardest, yet most rewarding, part of design is making things simple.
    </p>
  </StackedSection>

  <HumanCenteredSection>
    <p slot="body">
      At NBCUniversal and PragerU, I fostered team environments where critical thinking and candid feedback became expected. That foundation made usability testing, market analysis, and data-driven iteration more than process checkboxes; at PragerU, it's how I demonstrated the value of qualitative user testing to an executive team that was initially skeptical.
    </p>
  </HumanCenteredSection>

  <StackedSection
    id="unity-heading"
    heading="Unity nourishes your competitive advantage"
    imageSrc="/images/home/home-unity.png"
    imageSrcWebp="/images/home/home_unity_1x.webp"
    imageAlt="A collage of NBC News app screens across multiple devices"
    headingColor="var(--color-tan-dark)"
    textColor="var(--color-tan-dark)"
  >
    <p slot="body">
      Early in my career, <a href="https://x.com/sara_fortier" class="underline">Sara Fortier</a>'s work on <a href="https://outwitly.com/blog/creating-a-vision-for-ux-and-product-development/" target="_blank" class="underline">North Star Principals</a>. reshaped how I think about product leadership. Building a shared vision provides cross-functional partners a single point of alignment. When everyone is building toward the same outcome, collaboration stops being a process problem and becomes a competitive advantage.
    </p>
  </StackedSection>

  <LeadingByExampleSection />


  <ConnectSection />
</BaseLayout>
